text: Conospermum canaliculatum is a shrub endemic to Western Australia. The shrub has a dense and erect habit typically grows to a height of . It blooms between July and December producing white flowers. It is found in the Mid West and Wheatbelt regions of Western Australia where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== ==External links== Category:Eudicots of Western Australia canaliculatum Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 1848
